node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 13, 2021 tagging @itskaibax. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Kai Bax @itskaibax 8 steps to starting a social media marketing agency in 2021. Here is what learned from building a $100K per month agency. (A thread)'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 13, 2021 tagging @itskaibax. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Kai Bax @itskaibax 1. Pick a niche The key to building a successful marketing agency is to pick one niche and make it you sole focus. I work with eCommerce businesses because of how profitable that niche is.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 13, 2021 tagging @itskaibax. May be an image of text that says 'Kai Bax @itskaibax 2. Offer one service Offering multiple services creates complexity and low profit margins. Pick one service and gain absolute focus. That's one of the biggest secrets of successful agency owners. In my agency, we run FB ads for clients.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 13, 2021 tagging @itskaibax. May be an image of text that says 'Kai Bax @itskaibax 3. Focus on client results As an agency owner, your number one focus is alway client results. The better the results you provide, the more you can chage for tor your service and the longer your clients wil stay with you.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 13, 2021 tagging @itskaibax. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Kai Bax @itskaibax 4. Price your service service With eCommerce clients, we're able to charge anywhere from $4-10K per month, provided we deliver great results for them. That way you only need 2-3 clients to make $10K per month. And that is why focus on the eCommerce niche.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 13, 2021 tagging @itskaibax. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Kai Bax @itskaibax 5. Outreach Reach out to you potential clients with a personalized message using Email, Linkedin, Facebook, or Instagram and schedule a phone call with them. You should always keep your calendar full with sales calls.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 13, 2021 tagging @itskaibax. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Kai Bax @itskaibax 6. Sell your service Selling your service comes down to 2 key things: -Practicing your sales skills -Having an irresistible offer Make sure your offer is something your clients deeply desire. If your offer is not good, it doesn't matter how good your service is.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 13, 2021 tagging @itskaibax. May be an image of text that says 'Kai Bax @itskaibax 7. Deliver the service You have two options: -Learn the skills yourself -Hire a contractor While the profits are bigger if you do it yourself, having a contractor makes your business more scalable as you can put more focus on getting more clients.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 13, 2021 tagging @itskaibax. May be an image of text that says 'Kai Bax @itskaibax 8. Create systems and scale You need to create systems to: -Automate operations. -Acquire more clients. Once you have those things in place you're ready to scale.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 13, 2021 tagging @itskaibax. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Kai Bax @itskaibax Those are the key things that helped me scale my agency to $100K per month. If you'd like to see more content about building a social media marketing drop me a follow. agency'.
